# Permissions Rules (V2.1)

**Authority:** `00_architecture_authority.mdc`

## Source of truth

- **Edit:** `shared/rbac/permissions.ts`
- **Generated:** `backend/src/auth/permissions.ts` (AUTO-GENERATED — do not edit)
- After changes: `npm run build:backend`

## Backend guards

```typescript
requirePermission('financial.write')
requirePermission('reports.trial_balance.read')
requireCompanyAdmin()
requirePayrollAccessForPayrollPaths()
```

Mount-level or per-route on `modules/<domain>/routes/`.

## Frontend

- `hooks/usePermissions.ts` / `usePermission()` for UI gating
- Hide actions user cannot perform; backend must still enforce

## Role matrix (summary)

| Role | Typical scope |
|------|----------------|
| `super_admin` | All permissions |
| `company_admin` | Tenant admin + users |
| `accountant` | Financial write, reports, audit read |
| `sales_user` | Project selling subset |
| `read_only_user` | Read reports, no write |

Full matrix: `shared/rbac/permissions.ts` + tests in `backend/src/auth/permissions.test.ts`

## New feature checklist

1. Add permission constants to `shared/rbac/permissions.ts`
2. `npm run build:backend`
3. Guard backend route with `requirePermission()`
4. Gate frontend UI with `usePermissions()`

## MUST NOT

- Hardcode role name strings without using permission constants
- Skip backend guards because UI hides the button
- Edit `backend/src/auth/permissions.ts` directly
